=====================================================================
üìå SQL COMMANDS (DDL, DML, DCL, TCL, DQL)
=====================================================================

SQL commands are divided into categories based on **what they do**:
‚úî Create & modify structure  
‚úî Insert & manipulate data  
‚úî Control access  
‚úî Manage transactions  
‚úî Retrieve data  

====================================================================
BASIC DATABASE COMMANDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------
show databases;
use world;
show tables;
====================================================================


====================================================================
# 1Ô∏è‚É£ DDL (DATA DEFINITION LANGUAGE)
====================================================================

DDL commands deal with **database structure**.

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ CREATE
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to create database objects like table, database, view.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
create table student (
  id int,
  name varchar(50)
);

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ ALTER
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to modify existing table structure.

OPERATIONS:
‚úî ADD column  
‚úî MODIFY column  
‚úî DROP column  

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
alter table student add age int;

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ DROP
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Deletes table or database permanently.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
drop table student;

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ TRUNCATE
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Removes all records from a table (structure remains).

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
truncate table student;

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ RENAME
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Renames table name.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
rename table student to student_info;

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
# 2Ô∏è‚É£ DML (DATA MANIPULATION LANGUAGE)
====================================================================

DML commands deal with **table data**.

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ INSERT
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to add new records into table.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
insert into student values (1, 'Akash');

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ UPDATE
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to modify existing records.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
update student set name='Aman' where id=1;

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ DELETE
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to remove records from table.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
delete from student where id=1;

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
# 3Ô∏è‚É£ DQL (DATA QUERY LANGUAGE)
====================================================================

DQL is used to **fetch data** from database.

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ SELECT
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Used to retrieve data from table.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
select * from student;

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
# 4Ô∏è‚É£ DCL (DATA CONTROL LANGUAGE)
====================================================================

DCL commands deal with **permissions & access**.

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ GRANT
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Gives user access privileges.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
grant select on student to user1;

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ REVOKE
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Removes granted privileges.

EXAMPLE:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
revoke select on student from user1;

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
# 5Ô∏è‚É£ TCL (TRANSACTION CONTROL LANGUAGE)
====================================================================

TCL commands manage **transactions**.

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ COMMIT
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Saves changes permanently.

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ ROLLBACK
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Undo changes since last commit.

------------------------------------------------------------

------------------------------------------------------------
üîπ SAVEPOINT
------------------------------------------------------------
DEFINITION:
Sets a point to rollback partially.

------------------------------------------------------------


====================================================================
SUMMARY TABLE
====================================================================

DDL ‚Üí CREATE, ALTER, DROP, TRUNCATE, RENAME  
DML ‚Üí INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE  
DQL ‚Üí SELECT  
DCL ‚Üí GRANT, REVOKE  
TCL ‚Üí COMMIT, ROLLBACK, SAVEPOINT  

‚úî DDL ‚Üí structure  
‚úî DML ‚Üí data  
‚úî DQL ‚Üí retrieve  
‚úî DCL ‚Üí permission  
‚úî TCL ‚Üí transaction  

‚úî Important for:
   ‚Ä¢ DBMS exams  
   ‚Ä¢ SQL interviews  
   ‚Ä¢ Real-world database usage  

END OF NOTES
====================================================================
